{"question_id": "qa_00096", "pipeline_version": "qgen-0.1.0", "question_text": "A 67\u2011year\u2011old man with a history of heart failure and atrial fibrillation is admitted urgently for worsening dyspnea. He is on chronic anticoagulation and has developed anemia and thrombocytopenia. What is the most appropriate next step in managing his blood product needs?", "type": "intervention", "subject_id": 17607881, "hadm_id": 25925344, "time_zero": "2187-11-21 09:56:57", "time_zero_policy": "icu_intime_plus(+24h)", "gold_labs": [{"label": "Hemoglobin", "proposed_reason": "determines transfusion threshold in heart failure", "guideline_citation": {"pmid": "42218639", "claim": "guideline\u2011directed transfusion thresholds in heart failure", "verified": true}, "patient_value": 9.6, "unit": "g/dL", "abnormal_flag": true, "n_measurements": 9, "in_chart": true, "last_charttime_offset_h": -7.8}, {"label": "INR", "proposed_reason": "assesses bleeding risk before transfusion", "guideline_citation": {"pmid": "27885969", "claim": "INR thresholds for transfusion decisions", "verified": true}, "in_chart": false}, {"label": "Platelet Count", "proposed_reason": "evaluates thrombocytopenia impact on transfusion safety", "guideline_citation": {"pmid": "41114449", "claim": "platelet thresholds for transfusion in bleeding risk", "verified": true}, "patient_value": 118.0, "unit": "K/uL", "abnormal_flag": true, "n_measurements": 5, "in_chart": true, "last_charttime_offset_h": -7.8}], "gold_micro": [], "reference_answer": "Transfuse packed red blood cells to raise hemoglobin above 10 g/dL, while correcting INR to <1.5 and ensuring platelets >50,000/\u00b5L before proceeding.", "causal_chain": ["low hemoglobin -> reduced oxygen delivery to myocardium -> worsened heart failure symptoms -> transfusion to restore oxygen carrying capacity", "high INR and low platelets -> increased bleeding risk -> transfusion contraindicated unless corrected -> correct coagulation before transfusion"], "pubmed_ci