{"question_id": "qa_00097", "pipeline_version": "qgen-0.1.0", "question_text": "A 79\u2011year\u2011old male who underwent same\u2011day surgery is now exhibiting new anemia, thrombocytopenia, mild coagulopathy, and metabolic alkalosis. Determine the most likely cardiac complication and the next diagnostic step.", "type": "diagnosis", "subject_id": 12728191, "hadm_id": 27689162, "time_zero": "2121-06-07 08:00:59", "time_zero_policy": "icu_intime_plus(+24h)", "gold_labs": [{"label": "Troponin I", "proposed_reason": "to detect myocardial injury in the postoperative setting", "guideline_citation": {"pmid": "32059771", "claim": "Guideline recommends troponin measurement for suspected postoperative myocardial injury", "verified": true}, "in_chart": false}, {"label": "NT\u2011proBNP", "proposed_reason": "to assess for acute heart failure or volume overload", "guideline_citation": {"pmid": "30933827", "claim": "NT\u2011proBNP is recommended for diagnosing acute heart failure in hospitalized patients", "verified": true}, "in_chart": false}, {"label": "12\u2011lead ECG", "proposed_reason": "to identify arrhythmia or ischemic changes", "guideline_citation": {"pmid": "29233732", "claim": "ECG is essential for evaluating postoperative cardiac rhythm disturbances", "verified": true}, "in_chart": false}], "gold_micro": [], "reference_answer": "Acute postoperative myocardial injury (perioperative myocardial infarction).", "causal_chain": ["New anemia, thrombocytopenia, and mild coagulopathy -> suggests perioperative bleeding or hemolysis -> can precipitate myocardial ischemia", "Metabolic alkalosis and elevated lactate (within normal) -> indicates possible tissue hypoperfusion -> supports myocardial injury", "Troponin elevation and ECG changes would confirm acute myocardial injury"], "pubmed_citations": [{"pmid": "32059771", "title": "Guideline for the Management of Myocardial Injury in the Perioperative Period"}, {"pmid": "30933827", "title": "Guidelines for the Diagnosis and Man