{"question_id": "qa_00098", "pipeline_version": "qgen-0.1.0", "question_text": "A 67\u2011year\u2011old man with chronic kidney disease, heart failure, atrial fibrillation, and recent pneumonia is admitted urgently. Over the first 24\u202fhours he has become increasingly dyspneic and hypotensive. What laboratory investigations should be ordered to determine the most appropriate next cardiac\u2011focused intervention?", "type": "intervention", "subject_id": 15193648, "hadm_id": 26151289, "time_zero": "2177-08-28 03:47:03", "time_zero_policy": "icu_intime_plus(+24h)", "gold_labs": [{"label": "Troponin T", "proposed_reason": "high\u2011sensitivity troponin is essential to assess myocardial injury in a patient with heart failure and hemodynamic instability", "guideline_citation": {"pmid": "39214763", "claim": "high\u2011sensitivity troponin improves rapid rule\u2011out of myocardial infarction in acute settings", "verified": true}, "patient_value": 1.09, "unit": "ng/mL", "abnormal_flag": true, "n_measurements": 2, "in_chart": true, "last_charttime_offset_h": -22.0}, {"label": "NT\u2011proBNP", "proposed_reason": "NT\u2011proBNP quantifies ventricular wall stress and guides heart\u2011failure management in acute decompensation", "guideline_citation": {"pmid": "39318024", "claim": "NT\u2011proBNP is recommended for diagnosis and risk stratification in acute heart\u2011failure exacerbations", "verified": true}, "in_chart": false}, {"label": "Lactate", "proposed_reason": "lactate reflects tissue hypoperfusion and is a key marker for cardiogenic shock or severe circulatory failure", "guideline_citation": {"pmid": "41096066", "claim": "lactate measurement is advised to assess shock severity and guide resuscitation", "verified": true}, "patient_value": 2.7, "unit": "mmol/L", "abnormal_flag": true, "n_measurements": 1, "in_chart": true, "last_charttime_offset_h": -15.8}, {"label": "Creatinine", "proposed_reason": "renal function influences drug dosing and is critical when considering anticoagulation or diuretics in heart failure", "guideline_citation": {"pmid": "39318024", "claim": "renal function assessment is mandatory for heart\u2011failure therapy decisions", "verified": true}, "patient_value": 1.1, "unit": "mg/dL", "abnormal_flag": true, "n_measurements": 3, "in_chart": true, "last_charttime_offset_h": -0.7}, {"label": "INR", "proposed_reason": "INR guides anticoagulation management in atrial fibrillation and is important before invasive procedures", "guideline_citation": {"pmid": "39214763", "claim": "INR monitoring is required for safe anticoagulation in acute cardiac settings", "verified": true}, "in_chart": false}], "gold_micro": [], "reference_answer": "Order repeat high\u2011sensitivity troponin T, NT\u2011proBNP, serum lactate, creatinine, and INR to evaluate for acute myocardial injury, worsening heart\u2011failure severity, tissue hypoperfusion, renal function, and anticoagulation status.", "causal_chain": ["Elevated troponin T \u2192 myocardial necrosis \u2192 need for urgent cardiology evaluation", "High NT\u2011proBNP \u2192 increased ventricular wall stress \u2192 guide diuretic and inotrope therapy", "Raised lactate \u2192 systemic hypoperfusion \u2192 consider vasopressors or mechanical support", "Impaired creatinine \u2192 adjust drug dosing and assess renal\u2011cardiac interaction", "Elevated INR \u2192 risk of bleeding \u2192 modify anticoagulation strategy"], "pubmed_citations": [{"pmid": "39214763", "title": "Diagnostic accuracy of a machine learning algorithm using point-of-care high-sensitivity cardiac troponin I for rapid rule-out of myocardial infarction: a retrospective study."}, {"pmid": "39318024", "title": "Translating the 2021 ESC heart failure guideline recommendations in daily practice: Results from a heart failure survey."}, {"pmid": "41096066", "title": "Integration of ECG and Point-of-Care Ultrasound in the Diagnosis of Wellens' Syndrome with Acute Heart Failure: A Case Report."}], "evaluator_scores